Class freenet.client.FetchException extends Exception implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: -1106716067841151962L

Serialized Fields

mode

int mode
Failure mode

newURI

FreenetURI newURI
Try this URI instead. If we fetch a USK and there is a more recent version, for example, we will get a FetchException, but it will give a new URI to try so we can update our links, bookmarks, or convert it to an HTTP Permanent Redirect.

expectedSize

long expectedSize
The expected size of the data had the fetch succeeded, or -1. May not be accurate. If retrying after TOO_BIG, you need to set the temporary and final data limits to at least this big!

expectedMimeType

String expectedMimeType
The expected final MIME type, or null.

finalizedSizeAndMimeType

boolean finalizedSizeAndMimeType
If true, the expected MIME type and size are probably accurate.

errorCodes

FailureCodeTracker errorCodes
If there are many failures, usually in a splitfile fetch, tracks the number of failures of each type.

extraMessage

String extraMessage
Extra information about the failure.
